      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): honor workspace-only fs for native tools",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nWhen an OpenClaw agent sets `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=true`, OpenClaw-owned file tools enforce that boundary. Codex app-server code mode also has a native shell/filesystem surface, so OpenClaw must keep that surface inside the workspace without disabling unrelated native Codex features such as code mode, plugin config, user MCP projection, side-question mode, and hosted web search.\n\n## Summary\n- keep the Codex app-server native tool surface enabled for effective workspace-only fs policy\n- constrain effective workspace-only runs by downgrading Codex app-server `danger-full-access` to `workspace-write` before thread/turn startup\n- preserve explicit per-agent `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=false` as an opt-out from global workspace-only policy\n- resolve workspace-only policy from the active agent, runtime/session key, default agent, then global config\n- cover mixed-agent, global, default-agent, runtime-session, explicit per-agent opt-out, malformed-config, and app-server request behavior\n\n## Evidence\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/dynamic-tool-build.test.ts` passed locally: 1 file, 55 tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts` passed locally: 1 file, 115 tests\n- `CI=true pnpm tsgo:core:test` passed locally\n- `git diff --check` passed locally\n\n## Real behavior proof\nThe new app-server run-attempt regression proves an effective `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=true` run with configured `appServer.sandbox=\"danger-full-access\"` sends:\n\n- `thread/start.sandbox === \"workspace-write\"`\n- `turn/start.sandboxPolicy.type === \"workspaceWrite\"`\n- `turn/start.sandboxPolicy.writableRoots === [workspaceDir]`\n- `features.code_mode === true`\n- no `apps._default` denial patch\n\nThat proves the filesystem boundary is enforced through Codex's own sandbox payload while native code mode and non-filesystem native features remain available.\n\n## Notes\n- Per-agent `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=false` is treated as an explicit opt-out from a global workspace-only policy; omit the per-agent key to fall through to the global policy.\n",
        "branch": "fix/codex-workspace-only-native-tools",
